{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/pathIsAbsolute(fileName:)"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/pathisabsolute(filename:)"]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"title":"pathIsAbsolute(fileName:)","externalID":"s:4GLib14pathIsAbsolute8fileNameSbSPys4Int8VGSg_tF","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"func","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"pathIsAbsolute"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"fileName"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"text":">!) -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"roleHeading":"Function"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Returns ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if the given ","type":"text"},{"code":"fileName","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is an absolute file name.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Note that this is a somewhat vague concept on Windows.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"pathIsAbsolute"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"fileName","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"text":">!) -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On POSIX systems, an absolute file name is well-defined. It always","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"starts from the single root directory. For example “\/usr\/local”.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On Windows, the concepts of current drive and drive-specific"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"current directory introduce vagueness. This function interprets as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"an absolute file name one that either begins with a directory"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"separator such as “\\Users\\tml” or begins with the root on a drive,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for example “C:\\Windows”. The first case also includes UNC paths","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as “\\\\myserver\\docs\\foo”. In all cases, either slashes or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"backslashes are accepted.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that a file name relative to the current drive root does not"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"truly specify a file uniquely over time and across processes, as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the current drive is a per-process value and can be changed."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"File names relative the current directory on some specific drive,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"such as “D:foo\/bar”, are not interpreted as absolute by this","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"function, but they obviously are not relative to the normal current"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"directory as returned by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"getcwd()"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_get_current_dir()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"either. Such paths should be avoided, or need to be handled using","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Windows-specific code.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/pathIsAbsolute(fileName:)":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" if the given "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileName"},{"text":" is an absolute file name.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Note that this is a somewhat vague concept on Windows."}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/pathisabsolute(filename:)","role":"symbol","title":"pathIsAbsolute(fileName:)","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"pathIsAbsolute"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"fileName"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">!) -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/pathIsAbsolute(fileName:)","kind":"symbol"}}}